{"id":390728,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC8zOTA3Mjg=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/390728","title":"Stored XSS on scan.nextcloud.com","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","severity_rating":"low","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2018-08-05T16:34:39.000Z","submitted_at":"2018-08-05T16:34:39.000Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"is_organization_group_member?":false,"is_triager?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"5b66c571","url":"/5b66c571","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"/assets/avatars/default-14ffa99f59cd01423c64904352cc130ffcb6a802eadfd11777a54485749e60f2.png"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"verified":false,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":13291,"url":"https://hackerone.com/nextcloud","handle":"nextcloud","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/hsgut1vi1cv8housqai9cm9383yx/235acf2ba808c3a51a94888fb977392c26f8fb0ccf77a81a4546c5e4065c06f1","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/hsgut1vi1cv8housqai9cm9383yx/3f1ab5c6a9b6dadada1e6c8121700b884388bd0a43471fee1897a38ce57d0b2c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":false,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"pentest_retesting_ends_at":null,"profile":{"name":"Nextcloud","twitter_handle":"nextclouders","website":"https://nextcloud.com","about":"Access, share and protect your files, calendars, contacts, communication \u0026 more at home and in your enterprise."}},"has_bounty?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"submitted_by_team_member":false,"submitted_with_assistant":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2020-03-01T13:57:00.351Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2020-01-31T13:56:53.777Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"The scan.nextcloud.com engine fetches a 'status.php' content in order to extract some version number as well as installed flavors.\n\nWhile scanning a website, the following API-wise cinematic happens :\n\n    POST https://scan.nextcloud.com/api/queue (twice, gives the UUID)\n    GET https://scan.nextcloud.com/api/result/\u003cUUID\u003e\n\nThe first POST to /queue triggers a scan (/requeue works similarly), and the second request (GET) fetches a JSON describing the scan results.\n\nWhile all the data fetched in the attacker-controlled \"status.php\" file are safely escaped with escapeHTML (stripping a lot of unwanted characters, - you might want to double check that \\ is escaped as well.), the `data.url` isn't escaped, and is placed in a HTML DOM element as innerHTML\n\n{F328696}\n\nThis means that if an URL contains valid HTML, it will be interpreted upon loading the XHR answer. A poc has been done, scanning for `hack.pirate-server.com/heh\u003cscript\u003ealert(1)`\n\n    $ mkdir 'heh\u003cscript\u003ealert(1)'\n    $ ln -s ../status.php heh\\\u003cscript\\\u003ealert\\(1\\)/\n\nPOC : https://scan.nextcloud.com/results/166b377c-a24d-41b3-bcec-1ae57dd651c8\n\nWhen loading the results, the \u003cscript\u003e element is inserted, and an alert(1) pops :\n{F328697}\n\npoc demo :\n{F328698}\nend\n\n## Impact\n\nAn attacker - having tricked an user into accessing a trapped scan report - could gain arbitrary javascript execution in the context of `scan.nextcloud.com`, which is a subdomain of nextcloud.com.\n\nWhile this might not be critical, maybe a Content-Security-Policy of another nextcloud.com domain blindly trusts *.nextcloud.com.\n\nWhich could mean the standard XSS consequences : impersonation, secret stealing, proxying traffic, drive-by malware download, etc. etc.","weakness":{"id":62,"name":"Cross-site Scripting (XSS) - Stored"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":328696,"file_name":"Screenshot_from_2018-08-05_18-11-25.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/328/696/fd2651cadc56805c05f0f01dfc918ad7982c4a7a/Screenshot_from_2018-08-05_18-11-25.png?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22Screenshot_from_2018-08-05_18-11-25.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27Screenshot_from_2018-08-05_18-11-25.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQ7LJDW226%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T090637Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECkaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJIMEYCIQCxvgGhKx%2BVpEqUvezL17KsuPm%2BUxDuHLvhZceWu%2BMLqAIhAKkG5bpt5DEPe%2F7CLdJR4L%2BDQUwTeU28cpR2l5c4MMyFKroFCPH%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FwEQAxoMMDEzNjE5Mjc0ODQ5IgwMUob3a7Wf8TICztYqjgViynfEiRCC8olGPrkLidAHWLGmj48nASMs7AmMr7Ek3A0OT%2BI6dQ0GOIUdHU3LC%2BvrGRWptjyKphafiKIEbVCEPqSzXnu%2BvBPkrscx7Ah0%2BdcvicfLr9GnC1keUBHg2GALtZT0%2BGUooCo4V8aFudk0KTSU6HaYHyocVkIrysjQfv9UJH5%2FMbUwZ0uqkbGqY2y3%2FLsQZSJ3JfcYSDLqpbsGyQ1TAmzhRdpr0%2F9lSvhlYyfINIUWi11n7gQyngl1CX%2BMiUHRPzKTTJXvY2NSWpJQWa02tUBEhQZiILxNjkv3WUpGT%2FFf9u7RAH9nv0kIpWNeCRHobeALVnjghUSpxEkeQMj7PvdTsiMVDamTT7aNrEVHeQW5C5MuTf5GMbh7RHWHmbX3s3tknvVHCFsOXK1oyZTW2lKgcDABkFcqTcWXLus9NvAqFxfDwpflVgEGU%2B1xzu6Pb8j8eLGbOm0aXzqUfgZRSyD9dVLF1EiY5WJA4WG0Qk7FdQnNOpiv4pmutSJ1IflA0nSOUiPQxSpkVTyCvQI6vdWxGO7PltAoDXqaceKXD7QmUqwTukiaWI63eMOMvqXjcwsJDpXRiCAiTXGlDyK3jx%2FE2qkvCMoJzlUQiPgPRHeQIVdRaxzN5tXC8yR3%2FXtIods3WaaGKqIadpLfr7PVSFJSV7JedTsxMRYchkjnJakh3BhHjAnd4Qr7nYZRPtQpwQYc7oQkfK0bggIOIqOQurFHrSVKlq9mXggzvhTOzUuRA%2FGQU8inzC3UXWe13apF8dGt7who71b07j2LG2yh4T3YqvtH5PhU0NOCzxtLIy%2FIoatJK3XSXma9faipwvGWrtL4mUZIwaHOSBtOuo7cAX9orwpqKyTLNJYwxP3GzwY6sAFQZHXAhokH0bd%2FCBV8yJU9VeBe3jbpHpYjPY7L6CXPpSp8V8s0oyYvkSODtK5PbhnXJSypwbikfCemQU